Articles.Content:
Windows 10, 8Gb ram, Steam latest 64bit version of KSP.  R9 280X, Intel 4690k.
 
Is anyone having issues with the Space Center Tracking? Sometimes I go into the tracking station and there is nothing there, but I shut the game, restart, and everything comes back?
 
Then, I get into a ship, and want to select another ship as target, and again, nothing is selectable.  Doing a rendezvous isn't possible, as I can't select any other target ship.
 
Space Station One is NOT a vessel I have created.  This happened in unmodded and my modded install.  
 
Edited April 26, 2016 by kyrcant

I have the same problem. I experienced it several times in my current modded save. Wanna know what Space Station One is!

edit: using ksp_x64.exe, mods are KER, MJ2, RT, SCANsat, USI Life & tools, contractpacks

bug: on entering tracking station from KSC no button is clickable, esc doesn't take me back to KSC, either "Space Station One" is the only flight listed with 99d99h99m MET or no flights at all are visible in the list on the left. the map view looks crowded with the actual flights from the current save, but no interactions are possible.

 

Edited April 26, 2016 by MircoMars

Yes, I also encountered this error a few times.

Of the mods @MircoMars uses, I have KER, RT, SCANsat, USI Life and ContractPacks. My bet is on RT or SCANsat, but I really don't know.

As to ability to select other ships in Map mode, I think it depends on the level of your Tracking Station.

22 hours ago, garwel said:

As to ability to select other ships in Map mode, I think it depends on the level of your Tracking Station.

the last I noticed, the tracking station was tier 2. but you're able to select own vessels in the TS' map view from tier 1.

I'm finding this error reasonably often on a 64bit mac installation.  A restart clears it up, temporarily, but after one or a few further missions, when I go back to the tracking station, I am faced with it again.  It occurs with a variety of mods I was using, and also in stock.  As with the others, I'm using SCANSat and RT, as well as USI plus a whole lot more, but we have those in common.  Very frustrating.  I've been selectively removing mods and starting a new game, and I have yet to be able to avoid it. 

Edited April 27, 2016 by subitan

2 minutes ago, subitan said:

I'm finding this error reasonably often on a 64bit mac installation.  A restart clears it up, temporarily, but after one or a few further missions, when I go back to the tracking station, I am faced with it again.  It occurs with a variety of mods I was using, and also in stock.  As with the others, I'm using SCANSat and RT, as well as USI plus a whole lot more, but we have those in common.  Very frustrating.  I've been selectively removing mods and starting a new game, and I have yet to be able to avoid it. 

Follow-up, no exceptions in the log, and nothing obvious to suggest that something has gone awry.  

SCANSat seems to only be loading one ship (presumably the space station artifact that appears in this error).  RT seems to be loading info on a lot of debris that shouldn't exist anymore - I only have two debris elements in the game (the mun-shot late-stage engines that are in orbit), yet it's loading four or five different debris elements.  I am using StageRecovery, so it's possible they exist at this point in the game, but it's an oddity.  The filter toggles in the tracking station also misreport the number of items.  Lots of debris, twice the number of satelites and twice the number of ships.  What I can't tell is if RT is messing up, or if RT is simply consuming messed-up data.
